<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html lang="en" xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd" xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <title>wooki - Collaborative Writing</title>
    </head>
    <style>
        /*
         Theme inspired from kuler scheme : http://kuler.adobe.com/#themeID/617195
         2F2F32	6E6D65 	C9BB9B	FFD8A1	FF7351
         */
        body {
            background: #C9BB9B;
            font-family: Helvetica;
            font-size: 14px;
            text-align: center
        }
        
        #wrapper {
            width: 700px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            text-align: left;
        }
        
        a {
            color: #FF7351;
        }
        
        h1 {
            color: #2F2F32;
            font-size: 76px;
            font-family: Georgia;
            font-weight: normal;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px 0px;
        }
        
        h2 {
            color: #FF7351;
            background: #2F2F32;
            font-size: 30px;
            font-family: Georgia;
            font-weight: normal;
            padding: 40px;
        }
        
        h1 img {
            vertical-align: middle;
        }
        
        h1 a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #2F2F32;
        }
        
        p {
            margin: 20px;
        }
		
		ul {
			margin:20px;
			list-style:disc;
		}
		
		li {
			margin: 0px 20px;
		}
    </style>
    <body>
        <div id="wrapper">
            <h1><a href="${indexPage}"><img src="${asset:context:static/img/wooki_logo_C9BB9B.gif}" alt="wooki logo" />&nbsp;wooki</a></h1>
            <div class="body">
                <h2>We are really sorry, your browser is not supported by wooki.</h2>
                <p>
                    Some non-standard browsers, like Internet Explorer browsers family, are intrinsicaley oudated in terms of technical evolutions. 
					Unfortunalety your browser is one of them, and Wooki still does not support it.
					Supporting theses browsers would result in :
				</p>
				
				<ul>
					<li>reducing the global user experience quality to fit theses browsers requirement</li>
					<li>having a work overload by integrating them, and fataly working less on improving existing features and creating new ones</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Both consequences are not what we want for Wooki.
				</p>
				  
                <p>
                    You should use one of the following browsers: <a href="http://www.google.com/chrome">Chrome</a>, <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/firefox/">Firefox</a>
                    or <a href="http://www.apple.com/safari/">Safari</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
